SIMPLE: waterman
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Waterman
<hw>Wa"ter*man</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Watermen</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A man who plies for hire on rivers, lakes, or
canals, or in harbors, in distinction from a seaman who is engaged on
the high seas; a man who manages fresh-water craft; a boatman; a
ferryman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An attendant on cab stands, etc., who supplies water
to the horses.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>Dickens.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A water demon.</def> <rj><au>Tylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Watermanship</ent>⟦br⟧
